data.enText: poles and boards that are joined together to make a structure for workers to stand on when they are working high up on the outside wall of a building

value.def: Scaffolding consists of poles and boards made into a temporary framework that is used by workers when they are painting, repairing, or building high parts of a building, usually outside.
value.tran: (通常指室外的)脚手架(组)，鹰架
